Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Assessment for Attorney Fees in the amount of $1610.00 entered as ordered by the court on 09/20/22  to pay $50.00 monthly.  Final payment due by 06/20/2500. Failure to pay is a Civil Judgment.
Affidavit and order for payment of attorney fees and costs due from Milwaukee County signed.  Filed by:   GAMINO  LAW  OFFICES LLC  $1,610.00

Defendant Joshua N Woods appeared by video.  Attorney Sarah Zwach appeared by video for Joshua N Woods.  Attorney Julie Knyszek appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD. 
Review Hearing held.  Defendant has not started treatment.  Court will adjourn case for an in person review hearing date.  Case adjourned, Br. 41.
Review hearing scheduled for November 10, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Joshua N Woods appeared by video.  Attorney Megan Kaldunski appeared by video for Joshua N Woods.  Prosecuting attorney Julie Knyszek in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case set for a motion hearing. Defense motion to withdraw as counsel is granted by the court. Court conducted Indigency Hearing. Court found defendant is eligible for appointment of counsel by court. Defendant requested court appointed counsel and agreed to reimburse Milwaukee County for the expense. The court appointed Atty. Sarah Zwach to represent defendant in this matter at County expense and at the rate of $100.00 per hour. The court ordered the defendant repay the County at a rate of $50.00 per month beginning at the completion of the case, and then the 1st of each month there after. Court advised defendant failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. Signed, Distributed & Filed, Order Appointing Attorney at County Expense. Court cancels the review hearing on 9/12/22. Case is adjourned to Br. 41.
Review hearing scheduled for October 20, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Kaldunski contacted the requesting Court hear this case early.  Defense counsel needs to withdraw from case as she is leaving the firm.  Parties emailed new court date.  Case scheduled for 9/1/2022 at 8:30 am for Motion to Withdraw by zoom.

Defendant Joshua N Woods in court with attorney Megan Kaldunski.  Joshua Milder appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case in court for status conference. Parties are prepared to enter into a deferred prosecution agreement.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights and entered a plea of GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the guilty plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty.  Court WITHHELD entry of judgment of conviction and finding of guilt.  Deferred Prosecution Agreement, Plea Questionnaire/Addendum, and Jury Instructions, filed.  Court ordered case adjourned for review hearing. Parties are advised that effective August 1, 2022 this case will be assigned to Judge Audrey Skwierawski, Branch 41 in Room 501 of the Courthouse.  Review hearing scheduled for September 12, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant's Plea Questionnaire and Advisement Forms, filed.
Order Appointing Counsel, signed and filed.

Defendant Joshua N Woods in court with attorney Megan Kaldunski appearing as a friend of the Court.  Mark Thompson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case in court for pretrial conference. Defendant does not qualify for public defender representation. Indigency Hearing held. Court found defendant is eligible for appointment of counsel by the Court. Defendant agreed to repay Milwaukee County for the fees and expense paid by Milwaukee County. The Court appointed Attorney Kaldunski to represent defendant in this matter at County expense and at the rate of $100.00 per hour and defendant repay the County at a rate of $50.00 per month. Repayment to begin after the conclusion of the case on the 1st of the month and every month thereafter. Case adjourned to Branch 35.  Status conference scheduled for June 16, 2022 at 08:30 am.

DEFENDANT WAS ORDERED BY THE COURT TO REPORT TO THE MILWAUKEE COUNTY JAIL (CJF) TO BE BOOKED AND RELEASED BY 5:00 P.M. ON (4/16/2022). IF THEY FAIL TO APPEAR A BENCH WARRANT WILL BE ISSUED FOR THEIR ARREST.

Oral No Contact Order with R.D.K-E.
Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Joshua N Woods in court.  Ryan Jay Michaels appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant is advised that this case is assigned to Judge Rosa, Branch 35.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel. Defendant does not qualify for Public Defender representation. Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Case is adjourned for a Pretrial Conference in Branch 35.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for May 11, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 4/14/22 @ 2:30p
